HEADWORD: clintonia
<hw>clintonia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any temperate liliaceous plant of
the genus <gen>Clintonia</gen> having broad basal leaves and white or
yellowish or purplish flowers followed by blue or black
berries.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Clinton's lily.</syn>⟦br⟧
